 17 /**
 18  * Creates a new image parameter object and populates it with default values for
 19  * all values not explicitly given.
 20  *
 21  * @class ImageParameters parameter object.
 22  * You need not set any fields that can be read from the image descriptor that 
 23  * MakeImagePyramid creates. See the {@link bigshot.Image} documentation for 
 24  * required parameters.
 25  *
 26  * <p>Usage:
 27  *
 28  * @example
 29  * var bsi = new bigshot.Image (
 30  *     new bigshot.ImageParameters ({
 31  *         basePath : "/bigshot.php?file=myshot.bigshot",
 32  *         fileSystemType : "archive",
 33  *         container : document.getElementById ("bigshot_div")
 34  *         }));
 35  * 
 36  * @param values named parameter map, see the fields below for parameter names and types.
 37  * @see bigshot.Image
 38  */
 39 bigshot.ImageParameters = function (values) {
 40     /**
 41      * Size of low resolution preview image along the longest image
 42      * dimension. The preview is assumed to have the same aspect
 43      * ratio as the full image (specified by width and height).
 44      *
 45      * @default <i>Optional</i> set by MakeImagePyramid and loaded from descriptor
 46      * @type int
 47      * @public
 48      */
 49     this.posterSize = 0;
 50     
 51     /**
 52      * Url for the image tile to show while the tile is loading and no 
 53      * low-resolution preview is available.
 54      *
 55      * @default <code>null</code>, which results in an all-black image
 56      * @type String
 57      * @public
 58      */
 59     this.emptyImage = null;
 60     
 61     /**
 62      * Suffix to append to the tile filenames. Typically <code>".jpg"</code> or 
 63      * <code>".png"</code>.
 64      *
 65      * @default <i>Optional</i> set by MakeImagePyramid and loaded from descriptor
 66      * @type String
 67      */
 68     this.suffix = null;
 69     
 70     /**
 71      * The width of the full image; in pixels.
 72      *
 73      * @default <i>Optional</i> set by MakeImagePyramid and loaded from descriptor
 74      * @type int
 75      */
 76     this.width = 0;
 77     
 78     /**
 79      * The height of the full image; in pixels.
 80      *
 81      * @default <i>Optional</i> set by MakeImagePyramid and loaded from descriptor
 82      * @type int
 83      */
 84     this.height = 0;
 85     
 86     /**
 87      * For {@link bigshot.Image} and {@link bigshot.SimpleImage}, the <code>div</code> 
 88      * to use as a container for the image.
 89      *
 90      * @type HTMLDivElement
 91      */
 92     this.container = null;
 93     
 94     /**
 95      * The minimum zoom value. Zoom values are specified as a magnification; where
 96      * 2<sup>n</sup> is the magnification and n is the zoom value. So a zoom value of
 97      * 2 means a 4x magnification of the full image. -3 means showing an image that
 98      * is a eighth (1/8 or 1/2<sup>3</sup>) of the full size.
 99      *
100      * @type number
101      * @default <i>Optional</i> set by MakeImagePyramid and loaded from descriptor
102      */
103     this.minZoom = 0.0;
104     
105     /**
106      * The maximum zoom value. Zoom values are specified as a magnification; where
107      * 2<sup>n</sup> is the magnification and n is the zoom value. So a zoom value of
108      * 2 means a 4x magnification of the full image. -3 means showing an image that
109      * is a eighth (1/8 or 1/2<sup>3</sup>) of the full size.
110      *
111      * @type number
112      * @default 0.0
113      */
114     this.maxZoom = 0.0;
115     
116     /**
117      * Size of one tile in pixels.
118      *
119      * @type int
120      * @default <i>Optional</i> set by MakeImagePyramid and loaded from descriptor
121      */
122     this.tileSize = 0;
123     
124     /**
125      * Tile overlap. Not implemented.
126      *
127      * @type int
128      * @default <i>Optional</i> set by MakeImagePyramid and loaded from descriptor
129      */
130     this.overlap = 0;
131     
132     /**
133      * Flag indicating that the image should wrap horizontally. The image wraps on tile
134      * boundaries; so in order to get a seamless wrap at zoom level -n; the image width must
135      * be evenly divisible by <code>tileSize * 2^n</code>. Set the minZoom value appropriately.
136      * 
137      * @type boolean
138      * @default false
139      */
140     this.wrapX = false;
141     
142     /**
143      * Flag indicating that the image should wrap vertically. The image wraps on tile
144      * boundaries; so in order to get a seamless wrap at zoom level -n; the image height must
145      * be evenly divisible by <code>tileSize * 2^n</code>. Set the minZoom value appropriately.
146      *
147      * @type boolean
148      * @default false
149      */
150     this.wrapY = false;
151     
152     /**
153      * Base path for the image. This is filesystem dependent; but for the two most common cases
154      * the following should be set
155      *
156      * <ul>
157      * <li><b>archive</b>= The basePath is <code>"<path>/bigshot.php?file=<path-to-bigshot-archive-relative-to-bigshot.php>"</code>;
158      *     for example; <code>"/bigshot.php?file=images/bigshot-sample.bigshot"</code>.
159      * <li><b>folder</b>= The basePath is <code>"<path-to-image-folder>"</code>;
160      *     for example; <code>"/images/bigshot-sample"</code>.
161      * </ul>
162      *
163      * @type String
164      */
165     this.basePath = null;
166     
167     /**
168      * The file system type. Used to create a filesystem instance unless
169      * the fileSystem field is set. Possible values are <code>"archive"</code>, 
170      * <code>"folder"</code> or <code>"dzi"</code>.
171      *
172      * @type String
173      * @default "folder"
174      */
175     this.fileSystemType = "folder";
176     
177     /**
178      * A reference to a filesystem implementation. If set; it overrides the
179      * fileSystemType field.
180      *
181      * @default set depending on value of bigshot.ImageParameters.fileSystemType
182      * @type bigshot.FileSystem
183      */
184     this.fileSystem = null;
185     
186     /**
187      * Object used to load data files.
188      *
189      * @default bigshot.DefaultDataLoader
190      * @type bigshot.DataLoader
191      */
192     this.dataLoader = new bigshot.DefaultDataLoader ();
193     
194     /**
195      * Enable the touch-friendly ui. The touch-friendly UI splits the viewport into
196      * three click-sensitive regions:
197      * <p style="text-align:center"><img src="../images/touch-ui.png"/></p>
198      * 
199      * <p>Clicking (or tapping with a finger) on the outer region causes the viewport to zoom out.
200      * Clicking anywhere within the middle, "pan", region centers the image on the spot clicked.
201      * Finally, clicking in the center hotspot will center the image on the spot clicked and zoom
202      * in half a zoom level.
203      *
204      * <p>As before, you can drag to pan anywhere.
205      *
206      * <p>If you have navigation tools for mouse users that hover over the image container, it 
207      * is recommended that any click events on them are kept from bubbling, otherwise the click 
208      * will propagate to the touch ui. One way is to use the 
209      * {@link bigshot.Browser#stopMouseEventBubbling} method:
210      *
211      * @example
212      * var browser = new bigshot.Browser ();
213      * browser.stopMouseEventBubbling (document.getElementById ("myBigshotControlDiv"));
214      *
215      * @see bigshot.ImageBase#showTouchUI
216      *
217      * @type boolean
218      * @default true
219      * @deprecated Bigshot supports all common touch-gestures.
220      */
221     this.touchUI = false;
222     
223     /**
224      * Lets you "fling" the image.
225      * 
226      * @type boolean
227      * @default true
228      */
229     this.fling = true;
230     
231     /**
232      * The maximum amount that a tile will be stretched until we try to show
233      * the next more detailed level.
234      *
235      * @type float
236      * @default 1.0
237      */
238     this.maxTextureMagnification = 1.0;
239     
240     if (values) {
241         for (var k in values) {
242             this[k] = values[k];
243         }
244     }
245     
246     this.merge = function (values, overwrite) {
247         for (var k in values) {
248             if (overwrite || !this[k]) {
249                 this[k] = values[k];
250             }
251         }
252     }
253     return this;        
254 };
